There is thirdly to be conſidered,The third thing to be conſidered. Who ſhall behold this glory of the Lord. The words of the Text are, All fleſh. And this is not meant concerning univerſall humane fleſh, but only of that, which beareth in it the true circumciſion the fear of the Lord. It is ſaid in Ezechiel;
Ezechiel. 36.26. I will give you an heart of fleſh. And the Chaldee interpretation there is to this effect,
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 Et dabo vobis c • rtimens coram me ad faciendum voluntatem meam. That it is ſuch an heart as is in awe of God, and is inclined to do his will.
